SWING VOTE

01:04.519 --> 01:07.876
<i>After a hotly contested race,</i>
<i>Americans go to the polls today...</i>

01:07.890 --> 01:10.757
<i>in what promises to be</i>
<i>a very close election.</i>

01:10.860 --> 01:14.682
<i>The Republican Andrew Boone,</i>
<i>hoping to hold on to the Oval Office...</i>

01:14.697 --> 01:17.018
<i>by edging out...</i>

01:17.033 --> 01:19.331
<i>the Democratic challenger</i>
<i>Donald Greenleaf.</i>

01:40.590 --> 01:43.007
Bud...
Bud.

01:44.360 --> 01:45.019
Bud!

01:49.065 --> 01:50.507
I'll call...
I'll call him back.

01:51.233 --> 01:54.100
If we had a phone, you could.
Come on!

01:56.806 --> 01:59.400
Goddamnit! It's cold.

01:59.475 --> 02:02.376
We're gonna be late again.
You need a shower.

02:03.346 --> 02:05.371
Can't believe
you slept in your clothes!

02:16.859 --> 02:18.349
Leave me any hot water?

02:19.295 --> 02:21.889
I don't know.
Water heater fix itself?

02:23.833 --> 02:27.257
Christ, Molly! Why don't you
just take the day off, okay?

02:27.269 --> 02:28.930
I'll write you a note.

02:31.540 --> 02:33.974
Now!
I'm not going to tell you again!

02:35.144 --> 02:35.940
Get up!

02:45.655 --> 02:46.349
<i>Bud!</i>

02:47.189 --> 02:48.884
Alright, I'm coming!

03:23.993 --> 03:26.518
- What?
- Egg salad.

03:27.563 --> 03:28.257
Again?

03:29.065 --> 03:30.430
You like egg salad.

03:30.499 --> 03:35.027
Well, not every damn day I don't.
You could mix it up a little.

03:35.271 --> 03:36.329
We're on a budget.

03:36.739 --> 03:39.207
You wanna eat better?
Drink less beer.

03:41.844 --> 03:43.573
- Fine.
- Fine.

03:45.081 --> 03:48.881
- And don't forget today.
- What's... what's today?

03:49.452 --> 03:50.783
Election day, dummy!

03:51.053 --> 03:54.045
I'm supposed to do a report
on you voting, remember?

03:54.123 --> 03:56.921
I already told you before
I'm not even registered.

03:57.193 --> 03:59.377
I registered for you
in the mail.

03:59.395 --> 04:02.364
That's great,
I could get jury duty now.

04:02.565 --> 04:05.796
- It's your civic responsibility.
- It's my civic, my what?

04:05.968 --> 04:07.663
It's your civic responsibility.

04:07.670 --> 04:10.332
My civic responsibility?
Where you learning this crap?

04:11.607 --> 04:12.904
Mrs. Abernathy.

04:13.075 --> 04:15.270
Well, stay away from her.

04:16.846 --> 04:18.040
She's my teacher.

04:43.806 --> 04:44.602
Sign this.

04:47.610 --> 04:48.269
What is it?

04:48.878 --> 04:52.041
A questionnaire. I'm supposed
to ask you about your politics.

04:52.948 --> 04:55.143
Well, go ahead.

04:55.251 --> 04:56.309
I already filled it in.

04:57.720 --> 04:59.051
I wanted you to sound smart.

05:01.991 --> 05:03.424
Give me
the first question anyway.

05:07.163 --> 05:08.824
What's your political affiliation?

05:11.567 --> 05:15.059
Alright,
I'm a conscious objector.

05:15.571 --> 05:19.860
It's not a war, Bud. It's an election.
And you are an independent.

05:19.875 --> 05:23.402
Independent? Why in the hell
would I be an independent?

05:23.946 --> 05:25.368
Because the two party system...

05:25.381 --> 05:28.407
has neglected the needs
of the working poor.

05:28.818 --> 05:30.308
- Let me tell you something, baby...
- Here we go again.

05:32.888 --> 05:35.880
The voting doesn't count
for a goddamn thing.

05:36.158 --> 05:38.888
Just a way to make you feel
like you're in control of something.

05:39.461 --> 05:43.522
It doesn't matter who you vote for,
we can't afford insurance and...

05:43.532 --> 05:47.593
if you get sick, I'm gonna have
to start selling my blood again.

05:47.736 --> 05:51.558
Mrs. Abernathy said every vote counts.
It's a social contract.

05:51.574 --> 05:56.204
It's a social contract.
This Mrs. Abernathy is full of shit.

06:16.031 --> 06:17.931
Meet me at the polling place
after work.

06:18.634 --> 06:19.293
Fine.

06:24.506 --> 06:25.700
You forgetting something?

06:29.311 --> 06:32.712
Bud, screw this up
and I'm leaving you.

06:38.554 --> 06:39.384
Do good!

07:09.518 --> 07:10.075
Where...

07:12.488 --> 07:13.614
Where the hell is Dewey?

07:14.723 --> 07:15.883
He got laid off.

07:15.958 --> 07:18.449
Bullshit! He got insourced.

07:19.395 --> 07:20.362
Insourced?

07:20.562 --> 07:24.362
Insourced. Instead of exporting
our jobs to Mexico...

07:24.500 --> 07:27.128
they're importing Mexicans
to take our jobs.

07:27.636 --> 07:29.194
You're paranoid,
you know that?

07:30.005 --> 07:34.169
<i>Attention! The opening</i>
<i>this morning is officially cancelled.</i>

07:37.646 --> 07:40.046
I can't even read
the damn signs no more!

07:41.350 --> 07:43.944
Our days are numbered, fellas.
You mark my words!

07:44.353 --> 07:46.617
These hombres work twice
as hard for half the money.

07:46.889 --> 07:50.017
I just figure they need this job
twice as bad as us!

07:50.926 --> 07:53.087
Whose side are you on?

07:53.329 --> 07:57.322
I don't take sides, Lowell.
Just stating the obvious.

07:59.268 --> 08:01.702
Next thing, they'll be taking
away our right to vote.

08:02.738 --> 08:03.636
You voting, Bud?

08:04.273 --> 08:06.366
It's a social contract,
isn't it?

08:07.543 --> 08:09.101
Who are you voting for?

08:11.046 --> 08:12.445
Shit if I know!

08:16.218 --> 08:21.383
I think I picked up a couple shades.
Looks like an eight.

08:21.623 --> 08:22.647
What do you think, Marty?

08:24.093 --> 08:25.890
I don't like
the margin in Florida.

08:26.061 --> 08:29.724
Bus some young Republicans down
to the polling stations in Palm Beach.

08:29.965 --> 08:34.368
Make sure they're tall,
they're blonde and they're men.

08:35.270 --> 08:39.604
Because old Jews see a pack
of angry young white males...

08:39.741 --> 08:42.438
and they're gonna think twice
about getting out of their car!

08:43.679 --> 08:47.672
Kennedy was a nine.
And he put a man on the moon.

08:50.419 --> 08:53.604
That's what we need.
Something to shoot for.

08:53.622 --> 08:56.921
A defining moment.
Like... I don't know.

09:00.095 --> 09:01.221
Cure for cancer.

09:05.267 --> 09:08.020
Ohio run the gay marriage
ad every twenty minutes.

09:08.037 --> 09:10.426
Let's see if we can't get those God
fearing bastards off the fence.

09:10.439 --> 09:12.999
We take a bunch of scientists,
put them in the desert somewhere.

09:13.375 --> 09:16.594
Like the Manhattan project. Are you
listening to me? I'm serious about this.

09:16.612 --> 09:19.399
I think that cancer is going to be
a tough nut to crack in one term, sir.

09:19.415 --> 09:20.780
So, we make it a ten year plan.

09:21.083 --> 09:23.381
- Lincoln got to see the end of slavery?
- No.

09:23.852 --> 09:25.843
- Did Kennedy get to see the moon shot?
- Nope.

09:26.021 --> 09:30.117
No! But they got the credit!
It's the idea that counts.

09:30.259 --> 09:33.319
The guy that sets the goal
gets in the history books!

09:33.796 --> 09:37.687
Hope and positivity! Marty,
the American people want a bright...

09:37.699 --> 09:41.157
shining smile to represent
the promise of this country.

09:41.770 --> 09:43.101
Take old Georgie there.

09:45.074 --> 09:48.635
Boy, he was off the charts.

09:50.012 --> 09:51.309
They wanted to make him King.

09:52.815 --> 09:53.747
Son of a gun!

10:07.863 --> 10:10.161
Thank you,
thank you for coming.

10:11.733 --> 10:16.033
Galena and I would like
to thank America...

10:16.438 --> 10:18.633
for this glorious opportunity.

10:18.774 --> 10:22.733
I have met people of every race,
color and creed...

10:22.811 --> 10:24.608
during this long campaign.

10:24.780 --> 10:28.773
I pledge to you that my White House
will be a rainbow house.

10:28.851 --> 10:31.979
It'll be open to people
of all colors and creeds.

10:32.488 --> 10:35.855
Now, please, go and vote.
We need your support.

10:42.498 --> 10:44.056
That was great.
I'm gonna go do press.

10:44.199 --> 10:44.688
Great.

10:49.204 --> 10:53.436
Greenleaf! Greenleaf!

10:54.510 --> 10:56.205
Gallup has you down by a point.

10:56.278 --> 11:00.374
CNN, USA Today, has us up by two.
News has us down by sixty.

11:00.449 --> 11:02.747
What message are you trying
to get out to the undecideds today?

11:02.818 --> 11:06.140
The same message we put out yesterday,
last week and last year...

11:06.155 --> 11:08.715
when we started this campaign
and that's why we're going to win.

11:08.957 --> 11:12.518
Because we have the answers.
Not platitudes and jingoistic rhetoric.

11:12.694 --> 11:15.254
This is the truth
train operation real deal.

11:15.364 --> 11:18.925
In recent days, the president
has aired ads claiming Greenleaf...

11:18.934 --> 11:20.822
has vacationed
at a nudist colony.

11:20.836 --> 11:23.532
Come on, now, that's a tired
accusation. It's pure fiction.

11:23.705 --> 11:27.300
- Then, how do you answer for the photos?
- Right wing blogo-smear, that's how.

11:27.309 --> 11:31.234
I could stand here and perpetuate
the rumor that as a young man...

11:31.246 --> 11:34.841
the president had a gambling addiction,
but I'm got going to sink to their level.

11:35.284 --> 11:38.276
Despite eye witness
accounts and documentation.

11:38.287 --> 11:39.948
They sling mud,
we sling ideas.

11:40.022 --> 11:43.924
Still, if Greenleaf loses,
you'll be 0 for 7 on the national scene.

11:45.561 --> 11:48.997
Thank you, Betty. Sorry, folks,
that's all I have time for.

11:49.631 --> 11:50.598
Leeches!

11:52.501 --> 11:54.628
Why it's important to vote.

11:54.703 --> 11:57.467
Many brave soldiers
sacrificed themselves.

11:57.639 --> 11:59.402
A right we take for granted.

12:00.008 --> 12:01.999
- For the people.
- By the people.

12:02.311 --> 12:04.176
We the people!

12:05.214 --> 12:06.704
I can't read my writing.

12:07.416 --> 12:10.579
All the world's great civilizations
have followed the same path.

12:10.953 --> 12:14.548
From bondage, to liberty,
from liberty to abundance...

12:14.756 --> 12:18.852
from abundance to complacency.
From complacency to apathy...

12:19.194 --> 12:21.253
from apathy back to bondage.

12:21.330 --> 12:25.232
If we're to be the exception to history,
then we must break the cycle.

12:25.968 --> 12:29.460
For those who do not remember
the past are condemned to repeat it.

12:33.575 --> 12:35.634
Very good, everybody.
Very good.

12:37.479 --> 12:38.309
Hold this.

12:38.547 --> 12:42.142
Okay, remember, no running
till you get out to the playground.

12:42.584 --> 12:45.303
Your last one was great.
I'd like to use it on the news.

12:45.320 --> 12:46.184
- Molly?
- Yes.

12:46.421 --> 12:47.581
Molly, come here.

12:48.624 --> 12:51.843
This is Ms. Madison.
She's the reporter from the news.

12:51.860 --> 12:53.248
- Hi, Molly.
- Hi.

12:53.262 --> 12:54.490
- How you doing?
- Good.

12:54.563 --> 12:56.997
Your essay was very thoughtful.

12:57.332 --> 12:58.094
Thanks.

12:58.467 --> 13:00.992
Ms. Madison is going
to show your essay tonight.

13:01.003 --> 13:02.994
- Isn't that exciting?
- Yes, madam.

13:03.071 --> 13:06.507
Tell me something. What do you
want to be when you grow up?

13:09.678 --> 13:13.978
I go back and forth. Either
a veterinarian or chairman of the Fed.

13:18.687 --> 13:19.483
Where's Bud?

13:19.888 --> 13:24.382
Went to take a leak half an hour ago.
I heard his name over the loudspeaker.

13:25.661 --> 13:26.889
What'd you have for lunch?

13:27.262 --> 13:30.356
- Egg salad. You?
- Hard boiled.

13:35.837 --> 13:36.599
Hey, Bud.

13:39.508 --> 13:40.998
Just giving you a heads up.

13:43.812 --> 13:46.076
Management wants us
to cut another ten percent.

13:46.581 --> 13:50.779
Well,
you are management, Carl.

13:51.119 --> 13:54.418
Look, you haven't punched
in on time in six months.

13:54.656 --> 14:00.390
So, I'm five minutes late every once
in a while. What is the big whoop?

14:00.462 --> 14:04.159
You took thirty-one
sick days this year, Bud.

14:06.034 --> 14:10.027
Well, I gotta kid, Carl.
She brings it home from school.

14:29.024 --> 14:30.685
<i>Shit! Goddamnit!</i>

14:51.546 --> 14:53.741
Well, hell, Carl!

14:54.616 --> 14:57.517
You could have showed me
your footage when you walked in.

14:58.720 --> 15:03.054
I know we went to school together, Bud.
I've always liked you.

15:04.226 --> 15:07.024
You gotta give me one good
reason why I should keep you.

15:10.098 --> 15:11.360
Why I can keep you.

15:43.498 --> 15:44.590
All hellsabelle!

15:49.438 --> 15:50.962
Sorry you lost your job.

15:51.106 --> 15:54.041
That's alright, Henry. Just...

15:56.244 --> 16:01.705
As soon as take your money,
I'm going from fired to retired.

16:02.317 --> 16:04.046
- Hey, Bud!
- Yes?

16:04.486 --> 16:05.919
Molly is on TV!

16:07.823 --> 16:09.620
- <i>Apathy back to bondage.</i>
- Geez!

16:09.925 --> 16:13.691
<i>If we are to be the exception to history,</i>
<i>then we must break the cycle.</i>

16:14.529 --> 16:16.759
- Curly, what time you got?
- Nine past seven.

16:17.566 --> 16:18.191
God!

16:19.968 --> 16:22.630
God, man! Shit!

16:41.389 --> 16:42.720
Goddamnit!

19:24.119 --> 19:25.746
PLEASE,
INSERT YOUR BALLOT

19:25.754 --> 19:29.417
ERROR CODE - RESTART

20:32.053 --> 20:33.577
I hurt the top of my head.

20:34.489 --> 20:35.478
Come on, lay down.

20:47.268 --> 20:48.997
I'm so sorry, baby.

21:00.181 --> 21:01.671
I want to live with Mom.

21:07.522 --> 21:08.181
Me too.

21:23.404 --> 21:26.658
<i>New Mexico</i>
<i>is a classic swing state.</i>

21:26.674 --> 21:28.301
- <i>Mrs. Madison?</i>
- Speaking.

21:28.543 --> 21:31.307
<i>I'm calling</i>
<i>from the New Mexico election board.</i>

21:31.379 --> 21:34.132
- The what?
- <i>The New Mexico election board.</i>

21:34.149 --> 21:37.983
<i>Madam, did you cast your vote</i>
<i>at a Texico polling station last night?</i>

21:38.286 --> 21:40.311
I voted in the morning.

21:40.455 --> 21:42.343
<i>In the morning. Alright.</i>

21:42.357 --> 21:43.255
Is there something the matter?

21:43.558 --> 21:46.049
<i>No, no, sorry to bother you.</i>

21:46.060 --> 21:48.722
<i>It is amazing. With every state</i>
<i>but New Mexico reporting...</i>

21:48.930 --> 21:51.490
<i>we're now in a dead heat</i>
<i>for the American presidency.</i>

21:51.633 --> 21:54.625
<i>Each candidate with virtually</i>
<i>the same amount of electoral votes.</i>

21:54.702 --> 21:58.627
<i>270, the magic number to win.</i>
<i>This is a real photo finish!</i>

21:58.640 --> 22:00.904
<i>And it goes to whoever wins</i>
<i>the popular vote in the state.</i>

22:00.975 --> 22:03.705
<i>All five electoral college votes</i>
<i>then swing to that party.</i>

22:03.778 --> 22:05.996
<i>Well, they don't call it the land</i>
<i>of enchantment for nothing.</i>

22:06.014 --> 22:08.608
<i>Whoever takes New Mexico,</i>
<i>takes the White House.</i>

22:08.683 --> 22:13.916
<i>It's déjà vu again. 2000 presidential</i>
<i>election came down to Dade County.</i>

22:13.988 --> 22:19.051
<i>400 votes in the state of Florida,</i>
<i>out of a total of 105 million cast.</i>

22:19.060 --> 22:23.827
<i>If this is a certified tie, neither the</i>
<i>candidate would receive the majority.</i>

22:24.065 --> 22:27.694
<i>Do we even have a president</i>
<i>to deal with this?</i>

22:27.836 --> 22:30.964
<i>Pursuant to the 12th amendment, the</i>
<i>House of Representatives would decide.</i>

22:30.972 --> 22:32.894
<i>That hasn't happened since...</i>

22:32.907 --> 22:37.674
<i>John Quincy Adams defeated</i>
<i>Andrew Jackson back in 1824.</i>

22:37.812 --> 22:39.370
<i>We're talking rare.</i>

22:39.647 --> 22:42.810
<i>No, this isn't a great civics lesson</i>
<i>to the people of this country?</i>

22:43.051 --> 22:48.011
<i>If anyone in New Mexico didn't vote,</i>
<i>he be kicking themselves right now.</i>

22:48.022 --> 22:52.652
<i>The latest reports coming in,</i>
<i>Curry County still too close to call.</i>

22:52.760 --> 22:56.719
<i>This election is down to a single</i>
<i>county. Is this even possible?</i>

22:57.899 --> 23:01.665
Listen, John, there's only 653
registered voters in Texico.

23:01.736 --> 23:03.363
<i>And they've already</i>
<i>recounted those votes.</i>

23:03.438 --> 23:07.135
I know. With that information
and a dollar, I could buy a chalupa!

23:07.275 --> 23:09.743
Everyone I know who voted
has been personally called.

23:10.645 --> 23:11.703
So what?

23:12.013 --> 23:14.504
So, the election. The fact
that it's down to Curry County...

23:14.849 --> 23:16.783
it has something
to do with Texico.

23:17.819 --> 23:19.719
Oh my God. Call you back!

23:39.340 --> 23:39.669
Bud!

23:41.709 --> 23:42.232
Come on!

23:43.778 --> 23:46.246
God, my head!

23:50.718 --> 23:52.811
What? What time is it?

23:53.087 --> 23:54.486
There's some people
here to see you.

23:55.523 --> 23:56.251
Some people?

23:57.058 --> 23:58.252
They look official.

24:01.562 --> 24:04.463
- Child services?
- That's what I'm thinking.

24:16.377 --> 24:18.345
- Okay.
- Here we go.

24:23.785 --> 24:26.948
Mr. Johnson, we would have called first,
but you don't have a telephone.

24:27.388 --> 24:31.415
No, no, no, we got a phone.

24:31.993 --> 24:34.848
It's just not connected right now.
But I'm on it, you know.

24:34.862 --> 24:37.854
I'm not gonna say it's been easy
since the wife left, but...

24:38.032 --> 24:40.227
- we're getting on fine.
- Sure are.

24:40.435 --> 24:45.737
And I'm gonna pay these off, I swear.
Just as soon as I find a new job.

24:45.907 --> 24:47.966
- A new job?
- Yes.

24:48.209 --> 24:53.272
I used to be in this Willy Nelson
tribute band. I was thinking about...

24:53.281 --> 24:58.082
getting the guys back together again,
soon as our bass player gets paroled.

24:58.386 --> 25:01.184
And the drinking, I know it,
I know it looks bad.

25:01.689 --> 25:05.090
And licking that sucker
is at the top of my list.

25:05.593 --> 25:08.153
Please don't take away from me.

25:09.464 --> 25:11.227
I'll do anything you say,
I swear.

25:13.501 --> 25:14.968
She's just my only good thing.

25:15.636 --> 25:18.230
Mr. Johnson,
we're not from Social Services.

25:20.008 --> 25:20.565
No?

25:21.442 --> 25:23.034
We're from the State
Election Bureau.

25:23.745 --> 25:27.044
Fuck! Thank you, Jesus!

25:30.051 --> 25:33.384
I'm Secretary of State Brower.
And this is Attorney General Wyatt.

25:33.454 --> 25:36.252
Mr. Johnson,
did you cast your vote last night?

25:37.458 --> 25:38.618
Last night, did you vote?

25:39.560 --> 25:45.328
That's right,
it's my civic duty, isn't it?

25:45.566 --> 25:46.692
Indeed it is.

25:47.535 --> 25:50.504
Mr. Johnson,
is this your signature?

25:55.443 --> 25:56.375
I guess.

25:56.644 --> 25:57.963
You guess it's your signature?

25:57.979 --> 26:02.541
No, no. That's right.
That's my signature.

26:03.117 --> 26:04.379
Did you retain your stub?

26:05.753 --> 26:06.583
What stub?

26:07.021 --> 26:09.285
The perforated stub
on top of your ballot.

26:16.130 --> 26:21.830
Where's that perforated stub
that I gave you for your school project?

26:22.470 --> 26:23.232
I've got it.

26:35.683 --> 26:36.377
It's him.

26:36.884 --> 26:39.045
Yeah, it's him. What do you mean,
"him?" Me, him?

26:41.189 --> 26:42.486
Sir, your vote didn't count.

26:43.257 --> 26:45.748
Mr. Johnson,
it's our duty to inform you...

26:45.760 --> 26:49.628
that you are entitled to recast
your ballot in a timely manner.

26:50.264 --> 26:52.289
What if I don't want to?

26:53.768 --> 26:54.393
Bud!

26:56.604 --> 27:01.166
Alright then, how about if I, how
about if I just whisper it to you then?

27:01.175 --> 27:03.643
Right here we'd get it over with,
right now and you can listen too!

27:03.711 --> 27:06.043
No, sir, there are strict rules
and legal procedures.

27:06.114 --> 27:10.073
Legal shit. Shit, fellas,
I can't afford a lawyer.

27:10.384 --> 27:13.114
You're not in trouble.
You don't need a lawyer.

27:13.521 --> 27:15.819
However,
I will have to administer an oath.

27:16.057 --> 27:16.955
An oath?

27:17.024 --> 27:18.787
An oath. Please,
place your hand on the Bible.

27:21.429 --> 27:23.397
Do you, Earnest Johnson...

27:23.731 --> 27:26.859
swear to recast your ballot
in the spirit of the law?

27:27.435 --> 27:29.198
Yeah, yes, sure. Okay.

27:29.804 --> 27:30.532
So noted.

27:30.605 --> 27:34.200
A petition will be filed on your behalf
and a date will be set for your revote.

27:34.375 --> 27:39.005
Does this put me
on some sort of fast track list?

27:40.381 --> 27:42.645
You know, for like jury duty?

27:43.684 --> 27:47.745
Considering the gravity of this
situation, keep all of this a secret.

27:49.223 --> 27:50.053
Have a good night.

28:06.407 --> 28:07.101
<i>Sorry.</i>

28:08.075 --> 28:12.034
You should be! I could get into
all kinds of trouble because of you!

28:13.681 --> 28:14.841
Gosh, Molly!

28:14.849 --> 28:18.910
Why can't you
learn just to let things be?

28:19.253 --> 28:23.747
I told you this was important to me,
but you never listen!

28:33.668 --> 28:37.388
<i>Another astonishing development:</i>
<i>New Mexico Elections Bureau is reporting...</i>

28:37.405 --> 28:41.501
<i>a single irregular ballot is holding</i>
<i>up a final decision in the state.</i>

28:41.609 --> 28:45.272
<i>As I said, a single ballot.</i>
<i>That's one vote, folks!</i>

28:45.446 --> 28:48.734
<i>This really couldn't get any stranger,</i>
<i>MSNBC has learned that the voter...</i>

28:48.749 --> 28:51.274
<i>has been identified and has</i>
<i>agreed to recast the ballot.</i>

28:51.786 --> 28:55.779
<i>One voter will decide the fate</i>
<i>of the state's five electoral votes.</i>

28:55.923 --> 29:00.815
<i>On this bizarre day, no one</i>
<i>will soon forget, one American citizen...</i>

29:00.828 --> 29:04.787
<i>will effectively choose the next</i>
<i>President of the United States.</i>

29:06.033 --> 29:08.866
Apparently the electronic
voting machine malfunctioned.

29:08.936 --> 29:11.655
The ballot was scanned, but the machine
died before the vote was counted.

29:11.672 --> 29:12.559
It's an anomaly.

29:12.573 --> 29:14.973
No shit, Larry! What polling
station was the machine in?

29:15.042 --> 29:17.010
Texico, New Mexico, sir.

29:17.812 --> 29:18.938
Is that a place?

29:19.780 --> 29:21.839
Where the hell is Texico?

29:21.916 --> 29:23.679
New Mexico, sir, Curry County.

29:23.751 --> 29:27.016
New Mexico election law dictates
if a voter's right is violated...

29:27.088 --> 29:30.182
The voter shall be-entitled
to recast the ballot. I know.

29:31.392 --> 29:34.850
Alright, kids,
we're going to war.

29:34.962 --> 29:37.123
A map!
Somebody get me a map!

29:37.365 --> 29:41.461
There's one schmuck standing between us
and the White House. Find out who it is.

29:41.769 --> 29:43.202
We can't do that legally.

29:44.672 --> 29:45.570
Just find him.

29:51.379 --> 29:54.314
We were supposed
to my cytoplasm out of Jell-O today.

29:56.017 --> 29:58.770
What kinda kid would rather
sit in a crummy classroom...

29:58.786 --> 30:00.151
than be out here?

30:00.655 --> 30:04.113
What kind of father goes fishing
when he should be looking for a new job?

30:04.458 --> 30:07.018
The kind who would just like...

30:07.028 --> 30:10.964
to spend a little more time
with his daughter.

30:12.066 --> 30:12.828
That's who.

30:13.868 --> 30:15.597
- Fine.
- Fine.

30:18.906 --> 30:19.998
Anyway, I've been thinking.

30:20.508 --> 30:21.770
How refreshing!

30:23.778 --> 30:27.942
Jesus! You gotta quit being
such a smart ass all the time?

30:28.015 --> 30:30.984
And you've got to stop using Jesus
as a cuss word all the time!

30:31.419 --> 30:33.239
He's a billion people's Savior.

30:33.254 --> 30:35.347
Alright, fine, okay?
I get it.

30:36.424 --> 30:37.857
- Fine.
- Fine.

30:45.132 --> 30:48.420
I wish...
your mom could be here...

30:48.436 --> 30:50.996
to talk to you about
everything that's going on.

30:53.874 --> 30:55.239
I really do.

30:56.210 --> 30:59.907
No, she... no, she can't.

31:02.116 --> 31:03.105
She's just, she can't, baby.

31:07.855 --> 31:08.321
Bud.

31:12.660 --> 31:15.220
Next Tuesday, is bring
your father to school day.

31:17.498 --> 31:20.023
- So?
- I want you to come.

31:23.437 --> 31:26.133
