to ask you a few questions.

32:48.789 --> 32:51.155
You know, you're much prettier
than you are on the TV.

32:51.592 --> 32:52.479
Thanks. I would...

32:52.493 --> 32:56.122
Don't get me wrong,
you're pretty on the TV too.

32:57.331 --> 32:59.663
Just, we got an old set
that kinda "squirshes" you.

32:59.834 --> 33:00.630
Squishes everybody.

33:01.168 --> 33:03.193
I believe, Mr. Johnson.
I believe...

33:03.204 --> 33:04.831
You can call me Bud.

33:05.272 --> 33:08.730
Bud. I was hoping you
could tell me why those men...

33:08.742 --> 33:11.233
flew from Santa Fe,
to see you in the middle of the night.

33:18.786 --> 33:22.813
Well, actually, I kinda promised
to keep that a secret.

33:23.891 --> 33:26.416
You mean,
you're going to recast your vote.

33:28.329 --> 33:31.765
Well, shit, I guess that I guess
it ain't that much of a secret then.

33:32.600 --> 33:36.161
Now, listen, Bud,
you need to watch your language.

33:36.337 --> 33:37.463
- We're taping this for TV, okay?
- The language?

33:38.138 --> 33:41.107
Goddamnit, yes of course!

33:41.242 --> 33:46.646
The question now is, who you voted for
and are you going to vote the same way?

33:48.916 --> 33:50.747
Remind me again who's running?

33:51.685 --> 33:54.677
What you're saying is,
you're keeping an open mind?

33:55.689 --> 33:57.554
Yeah, that's...

33:58.058 --> 33:59.355
That's the kinda guy I am.

34:00.261 --> 34:01.250
You gotta be kidding me!

34:01.929 --> 34:03.954
This is OJ big. Bigger!

34:05.799 --> 34:06.823
I gotta call network!

34:08.202 --> 34:11.797
John,
let me break the story.

34:11.804 --> 34:13.534
I thought I was gonna die
in this shithole.

34:13.674 --> 34:16.268
You said that when the time was right,
you'd give me a chance. That's the time!

34:16.342 --> 34:17.503
We'll be back to a real market.

34:17.645 --> 34:21.467
The city! With elevators and Chinese
restaurants and crime and traffic.

34:21.482 --> 34:24.371
I got the tape
of Mrs. Zachary's prize winning sow.

34:24.385 --> 34:26.319
Screw Mrs. Zachary.
And screw the sow!

34:26.453 --> 34:27.476
You promised me.

34:28.322 --> 34:30.813
Get network on the phone.
Don't screw it up.

34:32.525 --> 34:34.619
- You won't regret it!
- Better not! Darlene!

34:46.072 --> 34:50.065
So... is your dad coming
to talk to our class?

34:51.812 --> 34:56.806
I don't know. Doesn't really leave
the house much since my mom left.

34:58.419 --> 34:59.477
Mine left too.

35:00.354 --> 35:03.323
She's pursuing
a singing career in Albuquerque.

35:05.025 --> 35:07.357
I'm going to move there
when she becomes a big star.

35:07.428 --> 35:09.225
And she's gonna take me
on tour and everything.

35:11.065 --> 35:12.862
She'll probably do
a concert in Austin.

35:14.401 --> 35:15.925
I could get you free tickets.

35:16.503 --> 35:19.063
Maybe.
Guess I could borrow my dad's car.

35:20.240 --> 35:23.869
I'll wait till he gets drunk.
Sometimes he passes out.

35:29.516 --> 35:31.074
Do you think
I could try your skateboard?

35:34.655 --> 35:35.314
Okay.

35:42.429 --> 35:46.832
I'm the king of Curry County, John,
and I've been 15 years at this desk.

35:46.900 --> 35:50.097
I feel for you, Ted.
Don't make me call security.

35:59.313 --> 36:01.178
Holy crap!

36:02.149 --> 36:04.447
You, desk! Sit!

36:05.119 --> 36:07.087
People,
we go live in 30 seconds!

36:07.221 --> 36:09.121
From this point on,
the news counts!

36:09.189 --> 36:13.558
So excited,
I got my accent back. My god!

36:15.629 --> 36:16.596
And cue graphics!

36:17.564 --> 36:18.428
And cue music!

36:19.500 --> 36:21.798
And cue!

36:22.236 --> 36:27.606
Good evening. This is Madison, coming
to you from Curry County, New Mexico.

36:27.775 --> 36:31.211
Over the last 24 hours,
the American political process...

36:31.278 --> 36:35.078
<i>has ground to a virtual standstill</i>
<i>as the world watches...</i>

36:35.315 --> 36:40.150
<i>waiting for the outcome of an election.</i>
<i>Today, I uncovered the identity...</i>

36:40.254 --> 36:43.052
<i>of the person the entire</i>
<i>world has been looking for.</i>

36:43.290 --> 36:46.691
<i>The one swing voter</i>
<i>who will decide the election.</i>

36:46.960 --> 36:50.452
<i>Those of you hoping to hear that</i>
<i>decision will be sorely disappointed.</i>

36:50.664 --> 36:53.895
<i>Because you are about to meet</i>
<i>a registered independent...</i>

36:54.034 --> 36:56.832
<i>who claims to be</i>
<i>keeping an open mind.</i>

36:57.604 --> 37:00.300
<i>Imagine,</i>
<i>on this man's shoulders...</i>

37:00.541 --> 37:03.442
<i>stands the future</i>
<i>of the free world.</i>

37:03.811 --> 37:05.244
Just the kind of guy I am.

37:07.147 --> 37:11.447
Let it never again be said,
that a single vote counts for nothing.

37:21.462 --> 37:21.985
Bud!

37:22.830 --> 37:23.319
Bud!

37:24.465 --> 37:25.090
What?

37:26.100 --> 37:27.624
There's some people outside.

37:28.102 --> 37:32.198
Geez, you gotta stop
waking me up like this, okay?

37:32.706 --> 37:33.934
You're gonna kill me.

37:34.007 --> 37:36.305
There are some people outside!

37:37.778 --> 37:38.506
People?

37:39.680 --> 37:40.544
God!

37:43.250 --> 37:45.218
No, not there! Out front!

37:45.953 --> 37:49.514
Oh, God... What now?

37:51.725 --> 37:53.920
- Dad, hurry up!
- Yeah, I'm going, honey.

37:56.930 --> 37:58.420
There's a lot of people
out there.

37:58.732 --> 38:02.293
Okay, honey, let's see
what the fuss is all about.

38:06.940 --> 38:07.668
<i>Is that him?</i>

38:08.776 --> 38:09.470
Bud!

38:10.544 --> 38:12.034
Mr. Johnson,
any decisions yet?

38:24.992 --> 38:27.517
- Holy shit!
- What do they want?

38:29.229 --> 38:30.161
I don't know.

38:34.268 --> 38:35.360
Go turn the TV on, baby.

38:44.311 --> 38:47.474
<i>We are in the midst</i>
<i>of a historic moment.</i>

38:47.614 --> 38:50.082
<i>The swing voter</i>
<i>has finally been identified.</i>

38:50.250 --> 38:53.481
<i>We go live now to a trailer</i>
<i>in Texico, New Mexico.</i>

38:53.887 --> 38:56.617
<i>Earnest Johnson made</i>
<i>an appearance just moments ago.</i>

38:56.924 --> 38:59.484
<i>Apparently, overwhelmed</i>
<i>by the media presence.</i>

39:00.160 --> 39:03.687
<i>And Mr. Landry, exactly how long</i>
<i>have you known Earnest Johnson?</i>

39:04.331 --> 39:07.232
<i>Earnest Johnson?</i>
<i>Hey, Earnest!</i>

39:08.268 --> 39:11.704
- <i>You mean Bud?</i>
- <i>We all grew up together.</i>

39:12.139 --> 39:14.198
<i>How do you think he's</i>
<i>shouldering the responsibility...</i>

39:14.208 --> 39:16.676
<i>of picking the next President</i>
<i>of the United States?</i>

39:18.812 --> 39:21.713
<i>Well, I'm sure that...</i>

39:22.583 --> 39:26.349
<i>Earnest is...</i>
<i>crapping his pants.</i>

39:29.256 --> 39:31.975
<i>He's a good guy.</i>
<i>He likes to treat them good.</i>

39:31.992 --> 39:34.017
<i>We used to light</i>
<i>the mesa back here on fire!</i>

39:40.968 --> 39:42.265
It's all my fault, isn't it?

39:42.336 --> 39:44.566
No! No, no, no, baby, no.

39:45.138 --> 39:49.040
None of this would have happened
if I hadn't let you down.

39:50.310 --> 39:51.470
What are we gonna do?

39:52.379 --> 39:53.038
Well...

39:56.383 --> 39:57.714
I'm gonna back these people up.

40:04.191 --> 40:06.216
Holy shit!

40:07.828 --> 40:08.852
There's so many!

40:10.764 --> 40:13.858
Ok, I'm just gonna go out there,
right? I'm gonna...

40:15.702 --> 40:19.866
I'm gonna walk out there and tell
those people it wasn't me who voted.

40:20.474 --> 40:21.736
No, you can't!

40:22.109 --> 40:23.076
Why not?

40:23.443 --> 40:25.638
You swore to that judge,
on a Bible and everything.

40:25.712 --> 40:27.942
What? That was the middle
of the night. That can't count!

40:29.449 --> 40:32.748
You were under oath, Bud.
Voter fraud is a felony.

40:32.853 --> 40:35.287
And one more felony
and they take me away from you.

40:35.422 --> 40:37.413
You're right. Shit!
I am down to one!

40:49.369 --> 40:50.336
What do we do?

40:55.842 --> 40:59.175
We lie. We have to.

41:01.982 --> 41:07.648
Okay, that's a good plan.
Just a little white lie is all this is.

41:07.721 --> 41:09.951
- Between us.
- Just between us.

41:10.557 --> 41:13.685
Who knows,
maybe this thing, all these...

41:14.895 --> 41:18.854
Maybe all these people,
they just go away.

41:55.936 --> 41:57.301
Stop! Stop!

42:39.446 --> 42:40.708
What the hell is this?

42:41.181 --> 42:42.614
The biggest space we could find.

42:44.918 --> 42:47.944
How we gonna do this?
Build a campaign around one man?

42:47.954 --> 42:50.354
- I don't know how to do this.
- You're gonna leave it to me.

42:50.524 --> 42:53.288
We're gonna win him, Don!
We're gonna win this guy.

42:53.560 --> 42:55.744
We got the issues on our side!

42:55.762 --> 42:57.514
- There you go!
- He's gonna love me!

42:57.531 --> 42:58.725
What's not to love?

43:02.803 --> 43:06.933
We're in trouble. I need you to dig up
everything you can on Earnest Johnson.

43:07.007 --> 43:08.463
Talk to his family, his friends.

43:08.475 --> 43:10.773
I want to know what he reads,
what television show he watches.

43:10.844 --> 43:15.304
His hobbies, his favorite foods,
his hopes, his dreams, everything.

43:15.849 --> 43:20.183
All we have to do is win
over one American mind!

43:20.887 --> 43:21.979
You know, I was just thinking,
Marty.

43:22.756 --> 43:24.883
I'd like to get to know
this Bud Johnson. Personally.

43:25.158 --> 43:26.125
Okay. Good.

43:26.960 --> 43:28.427
Maybe take him out
for some ice cream.

43:32.299 --> 43:32.958
Ice cream?

43:33.900 --> 43:35.561
What grown man
doesn't like ice cream?

43:39.372 --> 43:42.705
No higher education,
not much lower education.

43:43.009 --> 43:45.170
Divorced single father,
recently laid off.

43:45.245 --> 43:46.337
What's our first step?

43:46.513 --> 43:49.641
Put you in a room together. See if you
persuade him to come over to our side.

43:49.850 --> 43:55.686
I like it. Him and me in a room. Yes,
talking ideas, seeing what comes up.

43:55.789 --> 43:57.711
Great plan.
I'll get you some talking points.

43:57.724 --> 43:59.282
I'm good off the cuff already.

43:59.459 --> 44:04.283
Of course! We're just gonna get
an itty bitty think tank together.

44:04.297 --> 44:08.063
We'll run the data, see what you two
could possibly have in common.

44:08.869 --> 44:10.302
Your petition has been processed.

44:10.537 --> 44:14.997
And in accordance with New Mexico state
law, Chapter 1, Article 13, Section 11.

44:15.008 --> 44:19.297
Could you do us a favor and back
these news people up a little bit?

44:19.312 --> 44:22.304
We could barely
sleep last night.

44:26.386 --> 44:29.412
said voter Earnest Johnson,
is hereby authorized...

44:29.422 --> 44:31.413
to recast his vote 10 days
from today along official.

44:32.392 --> 44:35.020
And there's a fat guy there,
he keeps leaning on my truck...

44:35.028 --> 44:37.087
fixing his hair
in my side mirror.

44:42.502 --> 44:46.256
Said voter, Earnest Johnson,
is hereby authorized to recast his vote...

44:46.273 --> 44:49.731
10 days from today. Along official
documentary notification...

44:49.743 --> 44:51.836
to both state,
federal regulatory authorities.

44:52.345 --> 44:55.041
Bud, life's gonna be
a little different from now on.

44:55.482 --> 44:57.347
You'll need security
around the clock.

44:57.951 --> 44:58.576
For what?

44:59.019 --> 45:00.816
You're a household name.

45:01.154 --> 45:04.180
Every political nut job in the country
is gonna make their way down here.

45:04.324 --> 45:08.784
In 10 days, you gonna make the most
important decision in the free world.

45:08.862 --> 45:11.751
And it is our job to make sure
this thing comes off fair and square.

45:11.765 --> 45:14.734
So, if there's anything
that you think we need to know...

45:19.072 --> 45:19.834
Like what?

45:20.740 --> 45:22.605
Something
we may find out later.

45:23.743 --> 45:25.370
Better now, than later.

45:29.482 --> 45:32.542
No, sir,
there's nothing to know.

45:36.690 --> 45:39.250
Molly! Molly! Molly!

45:39.693 --> 45:42.526
- I don't believe it. She's his daughter!
- Who's his daughter?

45:42.596 --> 45:45.224
The Chairman of the Fed,
the girl that won the essay contest.

45:45.232 --> 45:47.359
Remember, I ran the story on her,
election day?

45:47.834 --> 45:50.769
This is perfect! The network wants
to do an interview with her daddy.

45:51.004 --> 45:52.926
I'm not going
to use this little girl!

45:52.939 --> 45:55.464
I've told you this before.
I have integrity, like Paula Zahn.

45:55.542 --> 45:57.294
I met Paula Zahn.

45:57.310 --> 46:00.006
Paula Zahn eats
where my friend is a waiter, alright?

46:00.080 --> 46:02.640
I don't want to hurt
your feelings, you're no Paula Zahn.

46:02.716 --> 46:03.774
No Paula Zahn?

46:03.883 --> 46:06.374
I booked this story.
It was me.

46:06.386 --> 46:10.516
Yes, that's why everybody here
is trying to rip it out from under you.

46:10.790 --> 46:14.282
You want a desk in New York,
you want a desk in Los Angeles?

46:14.394 --> 46:16.828
Forget everything you learned
in journalism school.

46:16.997 --> 46:21.900
This isn't new anymore. This isn't life.
This is bigger. This is television!

46:53.533 --> 46:56.388
<i>The Johnsons have been virtually</i>
<i>besieged inside their trailer.</i>

46:56.403 --> 46:59.304
<i>but we're lucky to be joined</i>
<i>by their pizza delivery man.</i>

46:59.472 --> 47:02.339
<i>How would you characterize</i>
<i>Earnest Johnson's state of mind?</i>

47:03.243 --> 47:05.507
<i>Mostly I'd say, he was hungry.</i>

47:05.612 --> 47:06.738
<i>He was hungry.</i>

47:07.714 --> 47:08.874
<i>Well, there you have it.</i>

47:08.882 --> 47:10.247
I ain't tipping him anymore.

47:10.517 --> 47:13.179
I ought to trim
Mrs. Hardy's elm.

47:13.887 --> 47:17.846
Looks like it's moving in our roof.
What do you think?

47:18.725 --> 47:21.285
Hard to tell.
What do you think?

47:22.762 --> 47:23.524
Definitely.

47:25.231 --> 47:27.893
<i>Since has become the most Googled</i>
<i>town in the world...</i>

47:28.134 --> 47:30.728
<i>narrowly edging out in Jihad.</i>

48:01.601 --> 48:02.829
Holy crap!

48:03.269 --> 48:04.531
- You Bud?
- Yeah!

48:04.671 --> 48:06.571
You're Richard Petty.

48:06.873 --> 48:07.669
You got it, man.

48:08.108 --> 48:10.406
Hold on. Honey!
It's the king!

48:10.710 --> 48:14.373
I got a friend down the road I want
you to meet. You wanna go for a ride?

48:17.684 --> 48:21.313
Yes!
could my daughter come?

48:21.488 --> 48:24.821
In that case, maybe you'd better
drive. Precious cargo and all!

48:30.397 --> 48:33.093
Just a minute, Mr. Petty.
Hey, Chubby!

48:33.700 --> 48:37.397
Just because it ain't rolling, don't
make it furniture! Back out of here!

48:38.705 --> 48:40.036
Come on, baby! We gotta go!

48:41.107 --> 48:42.369
You're Richard Petty!

48:50.950 --> 48:53.077
Molly! Get a picture, honey.

48:53.620 --> 48:58.387
If you told me two days ago
that I'd be driving your Dodge...

48:58.658 --> 48:59.886
- Did you get it?
- Yes.

49:00.160 --> 49:03.561
Get one more. Get it with my chin
out a little bit. Like that.

49:04.531 --> 49:05.429
Like a hero.

49:06.833 --> 49:08.164
I told you, you crazy!

49:08.468 --> 49:10.163
You ain't seen nothing yet.

49:38.431 --> 49:39.056
Bud!

49:40.233 --> 49:41.894
This is the President's plane.

49:44.471 --> 49:48.567
Hello, you be Molly. I'm Mr. Fox,
I work with the President.

49:48.975 --> 49:50.909
Hi.
Hi. Bud, Martin Fox.

49:51.711 --> 49:53.770
- Hello.
- How are you? Come in.

49:53.847 --> 49:55.576
Take your hat off please.
Your hat.

49:55.949 --> 49:58.315
So, this is the Johnson family.

49:58.885 --> 50:00.546
Welcome to Air Force One.
Hi, Molly.

50:00.753 --> 50:02.277
- Thanks for having us, sir.
- It's a pleasure.

50:02.489 --> 50:04.184
- Mr. President.
- Huh?

50:04.991 --> 50:06.049
Call him Mr. President.

50:08.094 --> 50:09.891
It's an honor, Mr. President.

50:10.063 --> 50:12.122
It's an honor to meet you, Bud.
May I call you Bud?

50:12.232 --> 50:14.291
Yes, Mr. President.

50:14.734 --> 50:15.632
Come on in, come on.

50:17.971 --> 50:18.699
God, this...

50:19.906 --> 50:22.704
This place
is it's really something!

50:24.577 --> 50:26.272
It's my little home in the sky.

50:26.980 --> 50:30.746
It's kinda,
like a trailer with wings.

50:31.651 --> 50:32.845
Fine analogy, Bud.

50:33.319 --> 50:36.288
Molly, I saw your speech
on TV the other night.

50:36.489 --> 50:37.478
Very impressive!

50:39.125 --> 50:42.185
- Say thank you, baby.
- Thank you, Mr. President.

50:42.195 --> 50:44.026
- You must be a very proud father.
- Yes, sir.

50:45.765 --> 50:49.701
God, I'm sorry.
Mr. President.

50:51.237 --> 50:54.593
You can see why she's definitely
the brains of our operation.

50:54.607 --> 50:57.041
I know what you mean.
we all need a Molly.

50:57.477 --> 50:59.308
Marty here, is my Molly.

50:59.579 --> 51:03.936
That's right. Molly,
I bet a smart kid like you...

51:03.950 --> 51:05.645
would love to see the war room.

51:06.586 --> 51:07.644
No, thanks.

51:07.654 --> 51:11.351
Why don't we have a peek and then your
dad and the President can have a talk.

51:11.424 --> 51:14.393
Go on, Honey.
Daddy has to talk to the President.

51:17.797 --> 51:19.162
She's a firecracker!

51:19.232 --> 51:22.133
Yes, sir, she's the whole deal!

51:23.570 --> 51:26.038
I wouldn't mind seeing
the war room, Mr. President.

51:26.739 --> 51:30.470
I'll show it to you later.
And please, call me Andy.

51:31.844 --> 51:32.776
- Andy?
- Yeah.

51:35.181 --> 51:37.809
Are you sure,
that-that other guy...

51:37.817 --> 51:40.377
I know, things can get
a little formal around here.

51:40.653 --> 51:43.121
Commander in Chief, running
the country and all that. Please.

51:43.623 --> 51:46.217
I am just an ordinary man,
like you...

51:46.593 --> 51:48.356
The kinda guy you can sit down
and have a beer with.

51:49.429 --> 51:50.760
Would you like a beer, Bud?

51:54.567 --> 51:55.158
A beer?

51:58.571 --> 51:59.265
No shit?

51:59.973 --> 52:00.735
No shit.

52:02.542 --> 52:03.531
Well, then...

52:04.877 --> 52:07.607
- Yes. Hell, yeah, Andy.
- Okay!

52:08.014 --> 52:09.948
David, would you get us
a couple of beers, please?

52:10.116 --> 52:12.243
- Thank you very much.
- So...

52:12.819 --> 52:15.652
you're gonna have some
story to tell your friends.

52:18.358 --> 52:22.556
I read about you in the paper.
They say you've never lost an election.

52:23.096 --> 52:26.623
That's right. You can learn
a lot from reading the newspaper.

52:27.433 --> 52:31.494
They also said that you don't
believe in anything anymore.

52:32.372 --> 52:34.203
Even if it meant
selling your mother's soul.

52:34.273 --> 52:37.868
No, see, no, see that's libelous,
Because my mother is a wonderful...

52:38.044 --> 52:41.172
wonderful, wonderful woman.

52:54.761 --> 52:56.524
If you met my mother,
you'd understand.

52:58.631 --> 52:59.825
You a football fan, Bud?

53:01.034 --> 53:04.561
Well, I'm an American, aren't I?

53:06.439 --> 53:08.464
I played a little in high school.

53:08.975 --> 53:10.306
Did you now? What position?

53:10.443 --> 53:11.432
I was quarterback.

53:11.878 --> 53:16.577
I always thought football was
a strategic game. A lot like diplomacy.

53:16.649 --> 53:20.301
You got your offense, your defense,
the President is like your quarterback...

53:20.319 --> 53:21.786
and the American voters...

53:22.588 --> 53:25.489
Well... they're like the coach.

53:27.427 --> 53:28.826
Never thought of it that way.

53:28.895 --> 53:30.487
Now the coach's job
is to make sure...

53:30.496 --> 53:34.557
that the right man has
the football at the critical time.

53:35.101 --> 53:37.069
I know exactly what you mean,
Andy.

53:37.970 --> 53:38.698
Do you?

53:41.541 --> 53:42.439
Maybe not.

53:46.245 --> 53:47.405
Bring in the football, please.

53:50.783 --> 53:51.249
Bud.

53:53.986 --> 53:55.044
You wanna hold the football?

53:56.756 --> 53:57.882
There's a football in there?

54:03.196 --> 54:05.221
That case holds
the launch codes...

54:05.765 --> 54:07.596
to America's nuclear arsenal.

54:09.068 --> 54:10.501
That's what
this election's all about.

54:11.771 --> 54:16.799
launch codes like...
missiles and shit?

54:16.876 --> 54:20.312
I want you to pretend
that America is a team...

54:21.247 --> 54:23.579
- and you're the coach.
- Okay.

54:23.649 --> 54:27.335
Let's say it's the 4th quarter. We've
got possession, but we're down by five.

54:27.353 --> 54:29.776
North Korea has us pinned
in our own fifteenth line...

54:29.789 --> 54:34.726
with one second on the dooms day clock.
What are you doing to do?

54:34.894 --> 54:39.957
Okay, you go long. The only thing
standing between victory and defeat...

54:40.466 --> 54:42.661
is a successful Hail Mary.
One play.

54:43.436 --> 54:44.994
Who are you
gonna give the ball to, Bud?

54:45.071 --> 54:48.393
Do you pin your hopes on some
liberal second string quarterback...

54:48.407 --> 54:51.638
who hasn't had five minutes
in the big show? Of course you don't.

54:53.713 --> 54:55.044
You do the smart thing.

54:55.681 --> 54:59.276
The only thing. You go
with your strongest arm, the man...

54:59.285 --> 55:01.219
who's carried you through the season,
who's never let you down.

55:07.393 --> 55:09.861
Bud, America's counting on you.

55:10.429 --> 55:14.058
Yes, sir.
I'm not gonna let them down.

55:14.600 --> 55:15.464
But, here.

55:18.371 --> 55:20.839
Wouldn't want to drop
the old football.

55:21.707 --> 55:23.072
Blow up France or something.

55:24.477 --> 55:25.193
You couldn't.

55:25.211 --> 55:29.841
There's a whole bunch of secret
codes and these special little keys.

55:30.383 --> 55:31.042
Here's to you!

55:33.519 --> 55:36.750
Look at all... Look at all
this stuff they give us, Molly.

55:37.390 --> 55:40.826
They give us the same shampoo
that the President uses.

55:41.227 --> 55:42.194
Great.

55:47.834 --> 55:49.961
So, what did you guys talk about?

55:53.372 --> 55:55.533
- Stuff.
- What stuff?

55:55.808 --> 55:56.832
You know...

55:58.611 --> 55:59.703
grown up stuff.

56:00.046 --> 56:01.035
Like?

56:02.215 --> 56:03.375
Like...

56:07.954 --> 56:08.579
Bud!

56:10.389 --> 56:11.583
What stuff?

56:11.657 --> 56:14.785
Like grown up stuff.
You know, coaching. Football.

56:15.361 --> 56:17.124
Geothermal nuclear war.

56:19.699 --> 56:22.099
Andy's, a great... great guy.

56:22.168 --> 56:25.695
He's not Andy.
He's the President of the United States.

56:25.838 --> 56:26.998
And he just wants your vote.

56:27.773 --> 56:30.298
And gee, guess what?
He's gonna get it.

56:30.409 --> 56:32.036
It's not even yours to give!

56:33.679 --> 56:34.338
You're gonna...

56:37.250 --> 56:38.649
ruin everything.

56:39.886 --> 56:42.684
Andy, the President,
invited me to watch the game...

56:42.855 --> 56:44.482
- with him on Monday night.
- That's a bribe!

56:44.490 --> 56:46.515
That's not a bribe.

56:46.592 --> 56:47.718
- Is too.
- It is not.

56:47.793 --> 56:49.021
- Is too.
- It is not.

56:49.095 --> 56:51.461
- Is too!
- Is not! What it is, "too"?

56:52.832 --> 56:54.857
- What the hell do you know?
- More than you.

56:54.867 --> 56:55.959
- You do not.
- Do too.

56:55.968 --> 56:57.731
- You do not.
- Do too.

57:01.641 --> 57:03.233
- Fine.
- Fine.

57:09.382 --> 57:11.714
Did you smell
all the leather on that plane?

57:17.924 --> 57:20.518
<i>If I made you feel second best</i>

57:22.428 --> 57:24.726
<i>I'm sorry I was blind</i>

57:25.631 --> 57:27.531
No, baby, leave it, leave it.
That's Willie.

57:29.802 --> 57:32.327
<i>You were always on my mind</i>

57:36.108 --> 57:37.234
<i>Hi, I'm Willie Nelson.</i>

57:37.243 --> 57:40.371
<i>And when I'm not performing,</i>
<i>I'm usually getting involved.</i>

57:40.780 --> 57:43.874
<i>Hey, Bud, if you're out there</i>
<i>and you're watching...</i>

57:44.283 --> 57:45.716
He's talking to us!

57:45.785 --> 57:49.642
<i>There's a special dinner,</i>
<i>especially for you in your honor...</i>

57:49.655 --> 57:55.321
<i>hosted by my good friend and</i>
<i>Presidential candidate Donald Greenleaf.</i>

57:55.561 --> 57:57.961
- <i>I'll see you here tonight.</i>
- I'll do it, Willie!

58:00.967 --> 58:02.832
This is really getting weird.

58:30.863 --> 58:32.387
Democrat or a Republican?

58:32.398 --> 58:35.834
I'm Art Crumb,
Donald Greenleaf's campaign manager.

58:36.102 --> 58:37.899
- Nice to meet you.
- Same here.

58:38.270 --> 58:43.207
You must be Molly. Quite an essay.
You have a future in politics one day.

58:43.542 --> 58:45.373
You might too. One day.

58:48.381 --> 58:49.109
Shall we go in?

58:52.018 --> 58:53.986
Not too hard to be nice,
come on.

58:54.787 --> 58:56.584
Party. Party!

58:57.490 --> 59:00.254
Right this way...
make yourselves at home.

59:02.929 --> 59:03.395
Hello.

59:03.864 --> 59:06.094
As you can see,
we've got a lovely buffet.

59:06.266 --> 59:07.597
Would you like a bud, Bud?

59:09.469 --> 59:10.094
Sure.

59:11.338 --> 59:15.434
Look at that.
You got chipped meat on toast.

59:16.276 --> 59:17.675
My momma used
to make that for me.

59:18.378 --> 59:20.096
- No kidding?
- Yes.

59:20.113 --> 59:21.808
There's all you can eat.

59:22.349 --> 59:23.373
It's all in your honor.

59:23.750 --> 59:26.344
And there's all the Willie Nelson
you can listen to.

59:26.620 --> 59:28.417
I understand
you're an aficionado.

59:28.622 --> 59:32.422
Yes, sir, I was in an all Willie
tribute band for about five years.

59:32.726 --> 59:34.250
Called ourselves
The Half Nelsons.

59:35.162 --> 59:36.220
Only his songs?

59:36.530 --> 59:39.363
No other request.
But you know, I got my own stuff.

59:40.600 --> 59:42.830
So, why don't you guys
do one of your songs tonight?

59:45.272 --> 59:49.675
I would but my rhythm
section's incarcerated.

59:50.510 --> 59:52.000
We've pulled a few strings.

59:52.212 --> 59:55.067
- Hey, Bud! Bud!
- Hey, boys!

59:55.082 --> 59:55.912
Come on up!

59:56.950 --> 59:57.974
They paying us?

59:58.051 --> 01:00:01.646
You really did, you got them out.
Thank you. Pull strings.

01:00:01.888 --> 01:00:06.882
Bud! Buddy, Buddy!
Buddy, look at me!

01:00:07.494 --> 01:00:11.897
Damn, Hank, you look good.
Just like prom.

01:00:13.433 --> 01:00:19.303
Thank you. Thank you, amigo.
This is the best day of my life.

01:00:23.343 --> 01:00:26.005
There's someone very
special I'd like you to meet.

01:00:27.514 --> 01:00:29.277
Mr. Johnson!

01:00:34.688 --> 01:00:36.178
Donald Greenleaf.

01:00:36.389 --> 01:00:37.185
Too tight.

01:00:45.165 --> 01:00:47.463
Hell of a party you got here,
Mr. Greenleaf.

01:00:47.534 --> 01:00:51.368
Yes, sir. We democrats
are one hell of a party.

01:00:52.706 --> 01:00:53.798
Call me Don.

01:00:56.776 --> 01:00:57.743
Okay, Don.

01:00:59.346 --> 01:01:00.335
The stage awaits.

01:01:04.684 --> 01:01:06.015
Well, he said so, right?

01:01:33.346 --> 01:01:35.940
<i>Pontiac, Pontiac</i>

01:01:36.149 --> 01:01:39.050
<i>Out there in my backyard.</i>

01:01:39.152 --> 01:01:43.612
<i>I'm gonna fix it up, paint it red</i>
<i>gonna make that engine go</i>

01:01:48.395 --> 01:01:50.886
<i>Chevrolet, Chevrolet</i>

01:01:51.097 --> 01:01:53.691
<i>Chevy year that running</i>
<i>Past fly, this and that</i>

01:01:54.100 --> 01:01:59.402
<i>Gonna make that engine go</i>
<i>You ready?</i>

01:02:01.808 --> 01:02:06.268
<i>They're all in my backyard</i>
<i>Them old cars</i>

01:02:07.314 --> 01:02:09.498
<i>I love everyone of them</i>

01:02:09.516 --> 01:02:12.007
Molly?
You remember me?

01:02:13.253 --> 01:02:14.481
Hi, Ms. Madison.

01:02:15.989 --> 01:02:17.889
Don't worry,
I didn't bring a camera.

01:02:19.960 --> 01:02:23.088
<i>I'm gonna get one running yet.</i>

01:02:25.098 --> 01:02:29.296
All this craziness.
I don't know how you're doing it.

01:02:34.040 --> 01:02:37.532
If you ever want to talk,
you call me anytime, okay?

01:02:38.211 --> 01:02:41.078
I'm gonna give you my card.
There you go.

01:02:44.451 --> 01:02:46.442
You want an interview
with Bud, right?

01:02:47.921 --> 01:02:49.218
I'd like him to think about it.

01:02:53.426 --> 01:02:54.120
Okay.

01:02:54.694 --> 01:02:57.527
<i>I'll get one running yet</i>

01:03:00.900 --> 01:03:02.925
<i>I'll get one running yet</i>

01:03:06.306 --> 01:03:08.638
<i>I'll get one running yet</i>

01:03:16.283 --> 01:03:19.252
<i>I'll get one running yet</i>

01:03:22.555 --> 01:03:24.853
<i>I'll get one running yet</i>

01:03:35.902 --> 01:03:37.529
Bud! You're the man!

01:03:41.975 --> 01:03:44.876
Well... I like you, Bud.

01:03:45.312 --> 01:03:48.679
You seem to be a real
genuine sort of guy.

01:03:48.748 --> 01:03:49.578
Thanks, Don.

01:03:49.849 --> 01:03:52.340
Tell me about yourself.
You got any hobbies?

01:03:53.119 --> 01:03:54.051
Just...

01:03:55.588 --> 01:03:56.953
just fishing.

01:04:00.360 --> 01:04:01.725
You're a fellow angler!

01:04:03.096 --> 01:04:04.495
What kind of rod do you use?

01:04:04.731 --> 01:04:09.395
Well, I use a six and a half foot
graphite Johnny Morris signature series.

01:04:10.437 --> 01:04:10.926
Heavy?

01:04:12.205 --> 01:04:13.069
Medium heavy.

01:04:13.940 --> 01:04:16.636
Bait catching reel,
twelve pound test.

01:04:18.511 --> 01:04:19.273
Don't tell me.

01:04:19.979 --> 01:04:23.608
Seven inch power grub,
purple shaky worm.

01:04:25.452 --> 01:04:29.411
Yes, sir! Damn, he, he,
you know your equipment!

01:04:29.622 --> 01:04:31.419
I figured you for a bass man.

01:04:31.658 --> 01:04:32.682
Well, I...

01:04:32.859 --> 01:04:35.259
try to take Molly out
as much as I can.

01:04:35.428 --> 01:04:38.192
We caught a two dinner stripe
on the Pecos just the other day.

01:04:39.132 --> 01:04:40.793
I'm sorry to hear that, Bud.

01:04:41.901 --> 01:04:42.560
Why?

01:04:42.869 --> 01:04:47.306
There's a bill in the House
targeting the Pecos River for...

01:04:48.308 --> 01:04:49.366
reallocation.

01:04:52.645 --> 01:04:53.873
You lost me there.

01:04:54.481 --> 01:04:56.881
That's where a big
corporation builds a dam.

01:04:57.317 --> 01:05:00.684
Limits the flow of water, the fish
can't get to their spawning grounds...

01:05:01.154 --> 01:05:03.520
eventually the whole
population dies off.

01:05:05.692 --> 01:05:10.254
That sucks, because I've been
fishing there my whole life.

01:05:10.597 --> 01:05:13.885
You'd better look for another river,
because President Boone has received...

01:05:13.900 --> 01:05:17.165
ten million dollars in contributions
from the energy company...

01:05:17.337 --> 01:05:19.669
and he's got to pay
them back somehow.

01:05:20.573 --> 01:05:25.067
Come on, now. Come on,
Andy wouldn't do that.

01:05:25.512 --> 01:05:28.447
He already did, Bud.
He already did.

01:05:30.717 --> 01:05:32.480
Okay. Can't you do something?

01:05:32.852 --> 01:05:34.319
If I'm elected President.

01:05:44.831 --> 01:05:45.320
What?

01:05:45.865 --> 01:05:48.299
No, tell me
exactly what was said.

01:05:50.170 --> 01:05:54.539
It's my commitment to protect
the wild places in this country...

01:05:54.908 --> 01:05:56.307
for future generations.

01:05:56.943 --> 01:05:58.740
And I'm not going
to stop there, Bud.

01:05:59.712 --> 01:06:02.306
With your help,
my administration...

01:06:02.515 --> 01:06:05.040
will be a leader
in environmental protections.

01:06:22.836 --> 01:06:24.064
My fellow Americans...

01:06:24.604 --> 01:06:29.735
I give you, the Pecos River
National Wildlife Preserve!

01:06:43.990 --> 01:06:47.687
And what can only be characterized
as a complete policy reversal...

01:06:47.794 --> 01:06:51.423
the President has surely
alienated his corporate donors...

01:06:51.498 --> 01:06:54.262
by adopting
a pro-environment stance.

01:06:54.667 --> 01:06:56.555
Bud and Molly Johnson
were on hand today...

01:06:56.569 --> 01:06:58.230
We are the environmental party!

01:06:59.572 --> 01:07:01.540
Those bastards
stole our platform.

01:07:02.342 --> 01:07:05.527
Put the PR people on standby.

01:07:05.545 --> 01:07:08.514
- You want Spiegelman Fischer?
- Too high brow.

01:07:08.815 --> 01:07:11.340
- What about those iPod guys?
- No, Larry, too urban.

01:07:13.520 --> 01:07:15.613
Get the guys
who do those Miller Lite spots.

01:07:15.688 --> 01:07:17.883
The ones with those girls
wrestling in the fountain.

01:07:18.258 --> 01:07:19.520
I don't know, Mr. Crumb.

01:07:19.592 --> 01:07:22.117
I like the narrator's voice.
His cadence.

01:07:23.563 --> 01:07:24.359
Just call them.

01:07:24.697 --> 01:07:28.189
Galena hates those ads, Artie,
she says they send the wrong message.

01:07:28.201 --> 01:07:31.170
Your wife's not our target demographic,
that son of a bitch is.

01:07:33.873 --> 01:07:34.737
Great.

01:07:36.609 --> 01:07:38.702
He's got the Secret Service
