Help me decide.

01:26:08.086 --> 01:26:09.542
Think about
what you're saying to me.

01:26:09.554 --> 01:26:12.785
I have! You should read
all this mail you've been getting.

01:26:13.258 --> 01:26:15.158
People are writing
to you for help.

01:26:15.627 --> 01:26:17.720
People are writing me letters.
So what?

01:26:18.230 --> 01:26:20.391
I can't help these people.

01:26:22.334 --> 01:26:23.562
You can speak for them.

01:26:27.939 --> 01:26:28.928
Will you do it for me?

01:26:35.147 --> 01:26:37.945
I'm doing this all
because of you!

01:26:42.954 --> 01:26:46.515
Confirmed, one Presidential debate
will occur this Wednesday night...

01:26:46.992 --> 01:26:50.120
at which Mr. Johnson will ask both
candidates a set of questions.

01:26:50.762 --> 01:26:53.094
The following day,
he'll cast his vote.

01:26:57.469 --> 01:26:59.460
Bud,
what will you ask at the debate?

01:27:00.539 --> 01:27:03.975
Truth is, I don't know yet,
but I'm...

01:27:05.510 --> 01:27:06.704
I'll figure it out.

01:27:12.951 --> 01:27:15.647
I hate debates.
Where they try-to trick you.

01:27:16.021 --> 01:27:17.989
I know, but you'll be fine.

01:27:18.824 --> 01:27:20.849
We have two days
to sew this thing up.

01:27:21.727 --> 01:27:23.456
I'm gonna need you
to meet with Bud again.

01:27:24.896 --> 01:27:27.797
And, offer him a little incentive.

01:27:29.534 --> 01:27:31.593
You want I give him
a bag of cash?

01:27:31.737 --> 01:27:33.602
No, he's got too much
attention on him for that.

01:27:34.139 --> 01:27:36.630
I was thinking
that maybe you'd offer him a job.

01:27:37.175 --> 01:27:40.201
Something with benefits.
If you know what I mean.

01:27:41.012 --> 01:27:42.707
Marty,
I've been meaning to talk to you.

01:27:44.850 --> 01:27:47.444
I'm not sure about our strategy
on this whole Bud thing.

01:27:47.886 --> 01:27:51.083
You've never questioned me before.
On anything.

01:27:51.790 --> 01:27:52.313
Ever.

01:27:52.891 --> 01:27:56.850
I know and I'm not saying
I won't do it. I just...

01:27:58.497 --> 01:27:59.964
I can't shake this feeling...

01:28:01.633 --> 01:28:04.500
The way we've been switching positions,
and now offering Bud...

01:28:06.471 --> 01:28:08.439
We're just doing
what we always do.

01:28:10.575 --> 01:28:11.166
That's all.

01:28:11.943 --> 01:28:15.174
Dancing the dance,
Courting the voters.

01:28:16.715 --> 01:28:19.616
Except this time,
it's only one voter.

01:28:21.453 --> 01:28:22.351
It's one guy.

01:28:23.522 --> 01:28:25.353
This is history,
Mr. President.

01:28:26.691 --> 01:28:28.283
It's never happened before.

01:28:28.827 --> 01:28:32.957
This is a moment the whole
world will remember. Forever.

01:28:35.467 --> 01:28:36.456
I understand.

01:28:43.308 --> 01:28:44.741
What are we about?

01:28:45.644 --> 01:28:46.201
Winning.

01:28:47.979 --> 01:28:51.415
Because if we don't win,
you can't do what you set out to do.

01:28:52.384 --> 01:28:54.318
And what you've done,
won't matter.

01:28:55.053 --> 01:28:58.113
If we don't win,
it's all over.

01:28:59.291 --> 01:29:00.349
And you're over.

01:29:01.893 --> 01:29:02.518
Bud!

01:29:05.964 --> 01:29:06.726
Bud!

01:29:10.769 --> 01:29:11.793
What time is it?

01:29:11.870 --> 01:29:14.964
Late. It's late.
You promised to take me in today.

01:29:15.040 --> 01:29:18.806
Okay!
Just give me a few minutes.

01:29:20.145 --> 01:29:22.670
What's today?

01:29:24.716 --> 01:29:25.648
Forget it.

01:29:28.954 --> 01:29:30.751
Can you take me, please?

01:29:33.325 --> 01:29:35.293
Yeah Ye. Let's go.

01:29:40.565 --> 01:29:41.589
Oh, God!

01:29:43.935 --> 01:29:46.460
Hey, wait a minute, Molly.

01:29:54.446 --> 01:29:56.573
Molly! Molly!

01:29:56.648 --> 01:29:59.583
Mr. Johnson... Mr. Johnson!

01:30:00.652 --> 01:30:02.279
The President
would like a word with you.

01:30:02.921 --> 01:30:04.616
- The President?
- Yes, sir.

01:30:07.459 --> 01:30:08.756
Hey, get a life!

01:30:10.962 --> 01:30:14.090
I used to work at Gilmore
before I got laid off.

01:30:14.833 --> 01:30:17.324
Now, I find work wherever I can.

01:30:18.570 --> 01:30:20.868
Mow people's lawns,
fixing stuff.

01:30:22.040 --> 01:30:23.132
Hasn't been easy.

01:30:26.544 --> 01:30:27.135
Molly.

01:30:29.948 --> 01:30:34.282
I'd sure appreciate it if your Dad could
put in a good word for me at the plant.

01:30:35.654 --> 01:30:38.714
Thank you,
Michael and Mr. Everett for that...

01:30:40.025 --> 01:30:41.014
presentation.

01:30:42.327 --> 01:30:43.624
Who's next?

01:30:44.329 --> 01:30:44.920
Molly.

01:31:01.746 --> 01:31:04.078
I guess you all
probably know my dad.

01:31:06.918 --> 01:31:08.909
He really wanted
to be here today, but...

01:31:10.555 --> 01:31:12.648
he had so many
important things to do.

01:31:14.759 --> 01:31:16.351
He's doing his best, but...

01:31:17.662 --> 01:31:19.493
he can't be everywhere at once.

01:31:22.300 --> 01:31:24.393
Ever since
all this stuff happened...

01:31:27.172 --> 01:31:29.367
he's really been
under a lot of pressure.

01:31:32.844 --> 01:31:34.607
I just want you to know that...

01:31:35.580 --> 01:31:38.447
he takes
his responsibilities seriously...

01:31:40.185 --> 01:31:43.621
and that he really cares
about helping poor people...

01:31:44.255 --> 01:31:45.654
and sick people.

01:31:47.392 --> 01:31:49.883
And people
that can't help themselves.

01:31:55.266 --> 01:31:55.891
My...

01:31:59.971 --> 01:32:03.031
my dad wants to make
this country a better place.

01:32:18.323 --> 01:32:19.984
Do you think much
about your future?

01:32:22.227 --> 01:32:23.285
What future?

01:32:24.863 --> 01:32:25.761
I know what you mean.

01:32:26.464 --> 01:32:28.523
We all worry
about the sun down years.

01:32:29.367 --> 01:32:31.699
Sooner or later,
all this hoopla is gonna die down.

01:32:31.970 --> 01:32:33.392
They're gonna build me a library.

01:32:33.405 --> 01:32:35.100
and you're gonna be
just another face in the crowd.

01:32:37.742 --> 01:32:38.606
Can't wait.

01:32:40.512 --> 01:32:42.207
What you need
to think about is security.

01:32:43.381 --> 01:32:44.541
Now I've got a friend...

01:32:46.484 --> 01:32:50.648
who might have a job for you.
In the lobby business.

01:32:52.190 --> 01:32:54.818
Like opening doors for people?

01:32:55.894 --> 01:32:56.792
Very astute!

01:32:57.328 --> 01:33:00.286
Open doors to politicians.
And their checkbooks.

01:33:00.298 --> 01:33:03.529
People really like you, Bud.
They feel like you're one of them.

01:33:05.103 --> 01:33:06.934
I'm not quite following you,
Andy.

01:33:13.344 --> 01:33:15.710
Sometimes you gotta figure
out what you want in this life.

01:33:17.215 --> 01:33:19.410
Then you have to decide
how much it's worth to you.

01:33:20.618 --> 01:33:22.415
Because they're gonna
put it on your tombstone.

01:33:24.389 --> 01:33:25.356
It's your legacy.

01:33:26.958 --> 01:33:28.892
A measure
of what you left behind.

01:33:30.829 --> 01:33:31.591
Are we...

01:33:33.865 --> 01:33:35.628
are we still talking
about the job?

01:33:38.369 --> 01:33:39.768
The lobby business?

01:33:42.607 --> 01:33:45.576
Right. Forget that.

01:33:50.048 --> 01:33:51.174
It's not worth it.

01:34:00.558 --> 01:34:01.422
And thank you.

01:34:36.027 --> 01:34:36.721
Molly!

01:34:37.996 --> 01:34:40.021
You said that
if I ever wanted to talk, right?

01:34:43.501 --> 01:34:44.763
Here's some hot cocoa.

01:34:46.538 --> 01:34:48.529
Sorry.
All I had was skim milk.

01:34:48.773 --> 01:34:49.671
It's okay.

01:34:52.744 --> 01:34:53.711
What's going on?

01:34:55.346 --> 01:34:57.814
- It's all my fault.
- What's your fault?

01:34:58.149 --> 01:35:00.208
Bud was supposed
to meet me after school.

01:35:00.418 --> 01:35:03.319
He knew how important it was to me.
But he got drunk.

01:35:04.088 --> 01:35:07.546
He never even showed up.
I didn't know what else to do!

01:35:07.559 --> 01:35:09.754
Wait, Molly,
what are you saying?

01:35:11.696 --> 01:35:12.287
Molly?

01:35:13.865 --> 01:35:14.957
Aren't you gonna get that?

01:35:16.401 --> 01:35:20.701
Yeah, give me two seconds. Stay here.
I'm gonna get them off the phone.

01:35:30.949 --> 01:35:35.886
<i>Can call you back?</i>
<i>This isn't a good time. Yeah, I know.</i>

01:35:37.222 --> 01:35:38.780
<i>I know.</i>
<i>You already told me that.</i>

01:35:46.831 --> 01:35:48.799
<i>Look, can I call you back?</i>

01:35:49.500 --> 01:35:50.159
Molly?

01:35:51.803 --> 01:35:52.497
Molly!

01:36:08.820 --> 01:36:09.445
Are you okay?

01:36:11.022 --> 01:36:13.013
You think your dad
might be passed out tonight?

01:36:16.928 --> 01:36:18.987
<i>Then,</i>
<i>you're going to recast your vote.</i>

01:36:19.097 --> 01:36:21.725
<i>I guess it ain't</i>
<i>that much of a secret then, is it?</i>

01:36:25.470 --> 01:36:29.338
<i>If we are to be the exception to history,</i>
<i>then we must break the cycle.</i>

01:36:29.941 --> 01:36:31.772
<i>For those</i>
<i>who do not remember the past...</i>

01:36:33.778 --> 01:36:35.712
<i>Remind me again who's running?</i>

01:36:35.913 --> 01:36:38.279
<i>So, what you're saying is,</i>
<i>you're keeping...</i>

01:36:38.750 --> 01:36:41.981
<i>It's all my fault. Bud was supposed</i>
<i>to meet me after school.</i>

01:36:42.120 --> 01:36:45.351
<i>He knew how important this</i>
<i>was to me. But he got drunk.</i>

01:36:45.757 --> 01:36:49.090
<i>He didn't even show up.</i>
<i>I didn't know what else to do!</i>

01:36:49.360 --> 01:36:50.645
<i>Molly, what are you saying?</i>

01:36:50.662 --> 01:36:51.651
He didn't vote!

01:36:54.599 --> 01:36:56.191
What do you mean,
she's missing?

01:36:56.200 --> 01:36:57.656
I'm sorry, Mr. Johnson.
It's all my fault.

01:36:57.669 --> 01:36:58.988
For crying out loud, Lewis!

01:36:59.003 --> 01:37:02.962
You guys guard Presidents.

01:37:04.709 --> 01:37:05.641
She's smarter!

01:37:08.279 --> 01:37:09.177
Tell me about it!

01:37:21.092 --> 01:37:22.354
What is all this?

01:37:23.394 --> 01:37:24.884
She's been answering your mail.

01:37:25.830 --> 01:37:26.455
For what?

01:37:29.200 --> 01:37:32.727
She wanted people
to think that you cared.

01:37:34.305 --> 01:37:35.237
She told you that?

01:37:49.454 --> 01:37:52.582
Does have any friends
we should contact?

01:37:52.657 --> 01:37:53.487
I don't know.

01:37:58.730 --> 01:38:01.824
No, she's not the friend type.

01:38:03.034 --> 01:38:03.591
Jed.

01:38:04.802 --> 01:38:07.589
- Jed? Who's Jed?
- It's a boy she likes.

01:38:07.605 --> 01:38:09.800
She likes a boy?

01:38:10.108 --> 01:38:12.099
Jed Barkley.
He's in her class.

01:38:12.276 --> 01:38:14.676
He's a little shy,
but they're friends.

01:38:15.413 --> 01:38:19.372
- Is she told you that?
- Yes, sir.

01:38:25.022 --> 01:38:26.649
Do you have any idea
where she might be going?

01:38:33.197 --> 01:38:36.132
Yeah, I'm can guess
where she's going.

01:38:36.667 --> 01:38:38.464
Just tell us where,
we'll go pick her up, sir.

01:38:41.339 --> 01:38:45.002
She's my daughter.
I'll get her myself.

01:39:11.669 --> 01:39:12.533
This is it.

01:39:14.372 --> 01:39:15.600
Sure you wanna go in?

01:39:17.375 --> 01:39:18.967
Came this far, didn't we?

01:39:20.878 --> 01:39:23.938
I'll wait here awhile.
Just in case you want to go home.

01:39:29.287 --> 01:39:30.754
I never want to go home.

01:40:06.290 --> 01:40:06.779
Yes?

01:40:07.992 --> 01:40:09.619
I'm looking for Larissa Star.

01:40:11.429 --> 01:40:15.866
Well, she's gone.
She's moved out a long time ago.

01:40:22.006 --> 01:40:23.132
I think you're her.

01:40:31.949 --> 01:40:32.711
You Jed?

01:40:34.886 --> 01:40:37.446
- It's okay, is she in there?
- Yes, sir.

01:40:39.657 --> 01:40:40.589
Wait here.

01:40:49.367 --> 01:40:50.527
You're all grown up!

01:40:51.936 --> 01:40:53.130
You look like your dad.

01:40:54.805 --> 01:40:56.363
He says I look like you.

01:40:57.341 --> 01:41:01.141
Does he?
So, why did you come here?

01:41:02.446 --> 01:41:06.314
You wrote me a letter.
You said I could come live with you.

01:41:07.485 --> 01:41:09.919
That was a long time ago,
honey.

01:41:11.722 --> 01:41:13.485
Things have changed.

01:41:14.659 --> 01:41:17.856
I'm close to getting
a record deal.

01:41:18.930 --> 01:41:20.795
I did a gig
a couple of months ago.

01:41:21.098 --> 01:41:26.491
This guy wants to put me in touch
with this big time Nashville producer.

01:41:26.504 --> 01:41:28.131
So he's gonna call me.
I'm not gonna be ready.

01:41:29.040 --> 01:41:32.999
I gotta get ready. There's a lot
I gotta do, so I can't do this.

01:41:34.712 --> 01:41:37.909
I'm not well.
Can't you see that?

01:41:39.884 --> 01:41:41.715
I can take care of you, Mom.

01:41:41.953 --> 01:41:45.047
I don't want anybody to take care
of me. I don't want you here.

01:41:46.223 --> 01:41:47.155
Dad!

01:41:50.828 --> 01:41:52.489
Jesus Christ, Larissa!

01:41:53.297 --> 01:41:55.015
I don't want her
to see me like this.

01:41:55.032 --> 01:41:58.763
Molly, you gotta go outside, okay?
For me. You got out there and wait.

01:41:59.236 --> 01:42:02.034
- Dad!
- Just outside. Now!

01:42:11.182 --> 01:42:14.276
I heard you'd finally
gotten cleaned up.

01:42:14.652 --> 01:42:18.281
Who told you that? My God,
what is going on out there?

01:42:18.356 --> 01:42:19.106
I can't explain.

01:42:19.123 --> 01:42:23.355
What are you, famous now? You think
you can just come? I can't do this!

01:42:23.461 --> 01:42:26.624
- Wait...
- No! No! Come here.

01:42:26.897 --> 01:42:28.182
I'm not mad Larissa.

01:42:28.199 --> 01:42:29.393
I'm trying to tell you...

01:42:29.800 --> 01:42:33.588
I can't be a mom right now.
I can't. Stay back! I can't...

01:42:33.604 --> 01:42:37.597
be a mom right now.
I can't do it. I can't do it.

01:43:50.281 --> 01:43:51.714
Said no reporters, Lewis.

01:43:51.916 --> 01:43:53.269
I just want to talk to you.

01:43:53.284 --> 01:43:54.717
I don't have time, Kate.

01:43:55.219 --> 01:43:59.576
I'm moderating a Presidential debate
tomorrow night in front of a zillion.

01:43:59.590 --> 01:44:03.253
So as much as I'd love for you
to make an ass out of me again on TV...

01:44:03.427 --> 01:44:05.019
I kinda have
some preparing to do.

01:44:09.400 --> 01:44:11.834
I have to catch up
on the issues.

01:44:12.903 --> 01:44:14.268
Like all of them!

01:44:14.839 --> 01:44:15.362
Bud.

01:44:19.043 --> 01:44:20.943
I know what happened
election night.

01:44:22.146 --> 01:44:25.309
I'm running the story. I just want
to make sure I've got my facts right.

01:44:25.783 --> 01:44:29.651
The bartender claims you
left the Starline about 7:30.

01:44:30.287 --> 01:44:30.981
Is that correct?

01:44:31.756 --> 01:44:32.518
Yes, madam.

01:44:32.957 --> 01:44:36.154
Giving you plenty of time
to meet at the polling station...

01:44:37.027 --> 01:44:38.085
and cast your vote...

01:44:38.729 --> 01:44:39.286
right?

01:44:42.399 --> 01:44:45.232
I... guess so.

01:44:46.670 --> 01:44:47.728
Just making sure.

01:44:50.608 --> 01:44:53.634
I'm sorry.
I got something for you.

01:44:57.114 --> 01:44:59.082
Kinda forgot who I was
for a moment.

01:44:59.950 --> 01:45:00.939
Forgive me?

01:45:02.119 --> 01:45:02.915
That depends.

01:45:04.655 --> 01:45:07.215
Can you help me,
help him tonight?

01:45:10.461 --> 01:45:11.393
I'd love to.

01:45:12.229 --> 01:45:14.993
I work two jobs
just trying to make ends meet.

01:45:15.599 --> 01:45:17.157
Last year my son
was diagnosed with...

01:45:17.168 --> 01:45:22.572
Law makers renewed the primary programs
for low income HIV and AIDS patients.

01:45:22.907 --> 01:45:25.842
Named for Ryan White,
a young AIDS activist...

01:46:46.423 --> 01:46:47.583
<i>Good evening everyone.</i>

01:46:47.791 --> 01:46:51.124
<i>We come to you live</i>
<i>from a small American town...</i>

01:46:51.629 --> 01:46:54.962
<i>a town most of us had never</i>
<i>heard of just a few weeks ago.</i>

01:46:55.165 --> 01:46:57.292
A town you couldn't find
on the map...

01:46:57.301 --> 01:47:00.759
because Texico, New Mexico,
wasn't on the map.

01:47:01.472 --> 01:47:02.837
<i>But it's on the map now.</i>

01:47:02.907 --> 01:47:06.707
<i>The whole world has descended</i>
<i>on this town for an historic event.</i>

01:47:06.844 --> 01:47:09.745
<i>A political debate</i>
<i>unlike any other.</i>

01:47:09.880 --> 01:47:12.474
<i>Tomorrow morning,</i>
<i>Earnest Bud Johnson...</i>

01:47:12.549 --> 01:47:15.211
<i>will walk into a voting booth</i>
<i>and make a choice.</i>

01:47:15.753 --> 01:47:20.884
And his choice will affect
our lives for generations to come.

01:47:21.458 --> 01:47:25.121
the stakes could not be higher.
What do you expect?

01:47:25.195 --> 01:47:29.063
I wonder, Aaron, what the founding
fathers would make of all this.

01:47:29.266 --> 01:47:32.963
Would they be mortified,
or would they be jumping for joy?

01:47:33.103 --> 01:47:36.334
Something tells me
that somewhere right now...

01:47:36.507 --> 01:47:40.967
Franklin and Jefferson
are looking down and smiling.

01:47:41.378 --> 01:47:42.902
Smiling or laughing?

01:47:43.080 --> 01:47:45.071
I don't know if they're smiling.

01:47:45.082 --> 01:47:48.415
That's not exactly who they had in mind
for picking the President of the USA.

01:47:48.585 --> 01:47:53.079
We're sending someone out there who
really is, as far as, we can tell lost.

01:47:53.223 --> 01:47:56.386
Can he find himself suddenly,
tonight on this stage...

01:47:56.527 --> 01:47:58.893
Or is he going to look
like a rodeo clown down there?

01:47:59.029 --> 01:48:03.193
Tonight, the whole country is
watching and we watch with you.

01:48:04.201 --> 01:48:05.532
I'm gonna puke.

01:48:05.602 --> 01:48:07.661
Bud, look at me. Look at me.

01:48:08.305 --> 01:48:11.035
Just be yourself.
You're gonna be great.

01:48:14.979 --> 01:48:18.005
Hey, remember dad.
No cussing! Okay?

01:48:18.482 --> 01:48:20.006
- Fine.
- Fine.

01:48:20.985 --> 01:48:22.919
Mr. Johnson,
one minute, please.

01:48:26.223 --> 01:48:27.121
Good luck!

01:48:31.762 --> 01:48:32.922
<i>And so we begin.</i>

01:48:33.364 --> 01:48:36.231
<i>The crowd has settled down</i>
<i>and we go to the stage...</i>

01:48:36.300 --> 01:48:37.767
<i>for what promises to be...</i>

01:48:38.302 --> 01:48:42.500
<i>one of the most unique moments</i>
<i>in American political history.</i>

01:49:25.916 --> 01:49:28.476
Mr. President, Mr. Greenleaf...

01:49:29.653 --> 01:49:33.054
I'd like to thank you for your
hospitality. It's been real interesting.

01:49:33.924 --> 01:49:36.518
I've said a lot of thing
I didn't mean.

01:49:37.327 --> 01:49:38.817
and you both
made a lot of promises...

01:49:38.829 --> 01:49:40.456
you probably
won't be able to keep.

01:49:49.840 --> 01:49:52.866
To be honest, the last 10 days
have felt like a weird dream.

01:49:53.710 --> 01:49:55.871
What was once kinda funny,
isn't anymore.

01:49:57.748 --> 01:49:58.942
From what I've read, I've...

01:50:01.118 --> 01:50:03.518
well, I've scared
the hell out of America.

01:50:04.488 --> 01:50:07.889
I know that the world is watching,
maybe even laughing.

01:50:08.358 --> 01:50:10.451
people on my own TV,
are saying...

01:50:10.727 --> 01:50:13.958
that America, somehow,
deserves this moment.

01:50:15.933 --> 01:50:17.230
Guess that means me.

01:50:20.104 --> 01:50:24.063
I can't say that I've been much
of anything most of my life.

01:50:24.141 --> 01:50:26.871
It's sorta like somewhere
along the way...

01:50:27.878 --> 01:50:31.700
I checked out and it's not like
I had big dreams to begin with.

01:50:31.715 --> 01:50:34.741
but I had something once.

01:50:35.953 --> 01:50:40.811
I had something close
to faith or hope or whatever...

01:50:40.824 --> 01:50:43.258
whatever word you want
to use for how good life could be.

01:50:45.095 --> 01:50:49.555
But then, the years start moving
quicker and all of a sudden...

01:50:49.566 --> 01:50:51.500
what's going good
out there for every else...

01:50:53.203 --> 01:50:54.693
isn't going so good for you.

01:50:56.039 --> 01:50:58.906
But, tonight I feel...

01:51:00.744 --> 01:51:01.642
embarrassed.

01:51:05.082 --> 01:51:07.448
I've had my chances,
more than most.

01:51:08.752 --> 01:51:10.344
I've grown up
in a country where...

01:51:10.687 --> 01:51:14.885
if I decided to do more with my life
than just drift and drink...

01:51:15.392 --> 01:51:16.984
that I could be standing where...

01:51:18.595 --> 01:51:20.256
where maybe you stand tonight.

01:51:21.031 --> 01:51:24.933
Instead, I've taken freely
and I've given nothing.

01:51:26.170 --> 01:51:27.637
I'm ashamed in front of my...

01:51:29.540 --> 01:51:30.165
daughter.

01:51:33.477 --> 01:51:34.535
And my country.

01:51:36.647 --> 01:51:38.831
I've never served or sacrificed.

01:51:38.849 --> 01:51:43.286
The only heavy lifting
I've been asked is simple stuff, like...

01:51:43.620 --> 01:51:46.851
pay attention. Vote...

01:51:49.560 --> 01:51:51.050
For America has a...

01:51:53.030 --> 01:51:55.965
if America has a true enemy tonight,
I guess it's me.

01:51:58.535 --> 01:52:02.528
Tonight a below average man is going
to choose between two exceptional men.

01:52:03.507 --> 01:52:05.998
Tomorrow, one man's vote
is going to make a difference...

01:52:07.377 --> 01:52:09.208
'Cause tomorrow
we're gonna have a President.

01:52:09.513 --> 01:52:12.107
And not just someone
to fill a chair in Washington.

01:52:13.817 --> 01:52:16.342
We need someone
who's bigger than their speeches.

01:52:17.321 --> 01:52:20.984
The kind of President
we learned about in school.

01:52:23.126 --> 01:52:24.787
America needs a big thinker.

01:52:27.164 --> 01:52:29.223
You know, like a giant, really.

01:52:29.566 --> 01:52:32.729
Someone who has the good sense
to get in front of our problems.

01:52:33.203 --> 01:52:36.366
somebody who has the wisdom
to lead to us a place...

01:52:36.373 --> 01:52:38.739
where we're at peace
with ourselves and the world.

01:52:40.711 --> 01:52:43.976
And just for the record,
I want you both...

01:52:45.215 --> 01:52:48.013
I want you both to know
that I think a hella lot of you.

01:52:58.862 --> 01:53:03.299
Tonight, I am going to speak
for people I have never met...

01:53:06.436 --> 01:53:09.337
whose letters touched me
in a way I didn't think was possible.

01:53:12.576 --> 01:53:14.544
My first question comes from...

01:53:14.845 --> 01:53:16.972
Peter Manthis,
in Henderson, Kentucky.

01:53:17.381 --> 01:53:18.575
"Dear Mr. Johnson...

01:53:18.782 --> 01:53:21.444
my wife and I
have three little girls.

01:53:21.518 --> 01:53:25.079
We both work two jobs
just trying to make ends meet.

01:53:26.723 --> 01:53:29.317
And some weeks,
we don't make it."

01:53:30.027 --> 01:53:32.882
"When you work hard and you still
can't take care of your family...

01:53:32.896 --> 01:53:36.525
you start to question yourself
as a provider, as a man.

01:53:37.668 --> 01:53:40.865
I know I am one. I fought
for my country and I'm proud of it.

01:53:42.572 --> 01:53:46.941
But it scares me to think about what
would happen if one of my kids got sick.

01:53:48.578 --> 01:53:53.015
"Can you ask the candidates,
if we are richest country in the world...

01:53:54.518 --> 01:53:57.510
how come some many of us can
barely afford to live here?"

01:54:00.624 --> 01:54:03.115
I'd like to take that one first,
if I might, Mr. Greenleaf.

01:54:04.194 --> 01:54:05.491
Answer, Mr. President.

01:54:07.731 --> 01:54:11.633
Bud, I'd first like to say, how much
I appreciate your thoughtfulness.

